cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper deals with learning Gaussian Graphical Models (GGMs) which are widely used in machine learning and natural/social sciences. The paper proposes new algorithms for learning attractive GGMs and walk-summable GGMs without any assumptions on the condition number of the precision matrix. This makes it likely to belong to the categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Information Theory (cs.IT), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
